---
description: Keep simple conditional guards and short conditional expressions on one line
globs: "**/*.{ts,tsx}"
alwaysApply: false
priority: high
---

# Single-line simple conditionals

When an `if` exists **only** to return a value (early exit / guard), put **`if`, condition, and `return` on one line**. Do not use a braced block for a single `return`.

Keep simple light-condition expressions on one line when they are readable:

- Short ternaries like `const languageModel = useMockAi ? createRatatouilleMockLanguageModel() : anthropic("claude-sonnet-4-20250514");`
- Short conditional initializers like `const [formCommitted, setFormCommitted] = useState(() => isFormMode ? props.defaultValue ?? "" : "");`
- Short hidden-value ternaries like `const hiddenFormValue = isFormMode ? (showInput ? draft : formCommitted) : null;`
- Short component signatures/destructuring like `export function RecipeListRowLink({ recipeId, title, thumbSrc }: RecipeListRowLinkProps) {`
- Short class-name constants such as `const previewZoneTitleClassName = "flex flex-col flex-1 justify-start gap-3 rounded bg-background/60 p-4 text-left text-base font-semibold transition-colors duration-150 group-hover:bg-background/86 group-focus-within:bg-background/86";`
- Short JSX tags with only a few props, such as `<button type="button" className={previewZoneGrowSectionClassName} onClick={onUploadZoneClick}>`
- Short labels/tags with a single `className`, such as `<label className={previewZoneGrowSectionClassName}>`
- Short icon JSX, such as `<IconUpload className={previewZoneIconClassName} aria-hidden />`

Terminate with a **semicolon** (see `semicolons.mdc`).

## Blank line after the guard

**Immediately after** the line containing the single-line guard, insert **one blank line** before whatever comes next. That separates the guard from the following logic (including another guard).

### Prefer

```typescript
if (!session?.user?.id) return new Response("Unauthorized", { status: 401 });

const userId = Number.parseInt(session.user.id, 10);
if (!Number.isFinite(userId)) return new Response("Unauthorized", { status: 401 });

let body: { messages: UIMessage[] };
```

```typescript
if (!isAiDebugEnabled()) return;

try {
  console.log(/* … */);
} catch (error) {
  console.error(/* … */);
}
```

```typescript
const [formCommitted, setFormCommitted] = useState(() => isFormMode ? props.defaultValue ?? "" : "");
const hiddenFormValue = isFormMode ? (showInput ? draft : formCommitted) : null;
const languageModel = useMockAi ? createRatatouilleMockLanguageModel() : anthropic("claude-sonnet-4-20250514");
```

```tsx
export function RecipeListRowLink({ recipeId, title, thumbSrc }: RecipeListRowLinkProps) {
  return <IconUpload className={previewZoneIconClassName} aria-hidden />;
}
```

### Avoid

```typescript
if (!session?.user?.id) return new Response("Unauthorized", { status: 401 });
const userId = Number.parseInt(session.user.id, 10);
```

```typescript
if (!isAiDebugEnabled()) return;
try {
```

## Avoid (multi-line guard)

```typescript
if (!session?.user?.id) {
  return new Response("Unauthorized", { status: 401 });
}

if (!Number.isFinite(userId)) {
  return new Response("Unauthorized", { status: 401 });
}
```

## Avoid (unnecessary wrapping)

```typescript
const [formCommitted, setFormCommitted] = useState(() =>
  isFormMode ? (props.defaultValue ?? "") : ""
);

const languageModel = useMockAi
  ? createRatatouilleMockLanguageModel()
  : anthropic("claude-sonnet-4-20250514");
```

```tsx
export function RecipeListRowLink({
  recipeId,
  title,
  thumbSrc,
}: RecipeListRowLinkProps) {
  return (
    <IconUpload
      className={previewZoneIconClassName}
      aria-hidden
    />
  );
}
```

## Exceptions

Use a **braced block** when the `if` body is not *only* a single `return`, or when the **`return` value must span multiple lines** (e.g. a large object literal, JSX, or a chained expression that the formatter breaks across lines). In those cases, normal multi-line formatting is fine. The **blank-line-after-guard** rule applies only to **single-line** `if (…) return …;` guards.

Use normal multi-line formatting for long JSX with many props, nested children, object literals, or expressions that become hard to scan on one line.

```typescript
if (error) {
  return {
    ok: false,
    message: error.message,
  };
}
```

## Scope

Applies to **new and edited** code in matched files. When editing legacy code, align touched guard clauses with this rule when it stays readable on one line.
